The paper deals with the computational complexity of various optimization problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of algorithms and computational complexity theory. The specific problems studied in the paper (partition, subset sum, knapsack) are all classic problems in these fields and are likely to be categorized under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), and cs.GT (computational game theory).
